File: The retail arm FNB took a 31 percent drop in normalised earnings at its retail segment. JOHANNESBURG - Financial services group FirstRand -- which owns FNB, Rand Merchant Bank and WesBank -- has taken a hefty profit hit as consumers struggled to repay loans. Headlines earnings were down 38 percent. The group noted a sharp increase in the number of customers applying for debt relief as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: FNB SA's most complained about bank - report More than 300,000 individuals applied. The retail arm FNB took a 31 percent drop in normalised earnings at its retail segment. No final dividend was declared by the bank.